properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 5 at 8:58AM PST until January 6 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, west winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts
up to 40 kt and seas 13 to 16 feet at 12 seconds. For the Small
Craft Advisory, southwest winds 15 to 25 kt.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Cape Flattery to Cape Shoalwater
out to 60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 6 PM PST this evening. For
the Small Craft Advisory, from 6 PM this evening to 7 AM PST
Monday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or
occurring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires
experience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly
recommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe
harbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.
